modules.description: Provides functions for producing and consuming messages from Apache Kafka topics, including message serialization, delivery confirmation, and offset management. Works with byte sequences, message headers, and Kafka-specific error codes. Used to integrate real-time data pipelines, log aggregation, and event sourcing systems.

Provides functions to create and manage Kafka producers and consumers, send messages to specific topics and partitions, and read messages from topics. Operates with types such as producer, consumer, and Kafka.topic, and returns results wrapped in a custom response type. Used to asynchronously publish events to Kafka and consume messages from specific topics in real-time.
